docs.abstract: New rules will require online services to overhaul how they treat the personal details of children in the country.
docs.snippet: New rules will require online services to overhaul how they treat the personal details of children in the country.
docs.lead_paragraph: Britain unveiled sweeping new online protections for children on Tuesday, issuing expansive rules despite widespread objections from a number of tech companies and trade groups.

headline.main: Britain Plans Vast Privacy Protections for Children
headline.print_headline: Britain Unveils Vast Privacy Protections for Children

docs.abstract: The Amazon founder’s investigation did not find evidence to back his suggestion of a link between Saudi Arabia and the tabloid that gleefully exposed his affair.
docs.snippet: The Amazon founder’s investigation did not find evidence to back his suggestion of a link between Saudi Arabia and the tabloid that gleefully exposed his affair.
docs.lead_paragraph: Almost a year ago, Jeff Bezos hinted that Saudi Arabia had played a role in The National Enquirer’s 11-page exposé of his affair with the Los Angeles television personality Lauren Sanchez. In making the case in a post on the website Medium, Mr. Bezos noted that his newspaper, The Washington Post, had published the Saudi dissident Jamal Khashoggi and had also covered the kingdom’s suspected role in his murder.

headline.main: Jeff Bezos’ Hack Inquiry Falls Short of Implicating National Enquirer
headline.print_headline: Hot Love! Tabloids Embrace New Bezos

byline.original: By Jim Rutenberg and Michael Rothfeld

docs.abstract: The Carlyle Group, an investor in her catalog, has stepped in to encourage talks between Ms. Swift and Scooter Braun, who now controls her old label.
docs.snippet: The Carlyle Group, an investor in her catalog, has stepped in to encourage talks between Ms. Swift and Scooter Braun, who now controls her old label.
docs.lead_paragraph: A little over a week ago, a troubling alert appeared on the smartphone of an executive at the private equity giant the Carlyle Group: The firm had been invoked by Taylor Swift.

headline.main: How Taylor Swift Dragged Private Equity Into Her Fight Over Music Rights
headline.print_headline: Taylor Swift, Equity Giant And a Feud

docs.abstract: Officials, breaking their silence, said they would tighten immigration procedures and investigate how the fallen auto executive was able to elude tight surveillance.
docs.snippet: Officials, breaking their silence, said they would tighten immigration procedures and investigate how the fallen auto executive was able to elude tight surveillance.
docs.lead_paragraph: TOKYO — Japanese officials on Sunday defended the country’s justice system as fair and open and condemned Carlos Ghosn’s flight from criminal charges there, as its courts are put under a global spotlight for their treatment of suspects and a near-perfect conviction record by prosecutors.

headline.main: Japan Defends Its Justice System After Carlos Ghosn’s Flight
headline.print_headline: Ghosn Flight Puts Japan On Defensive About Courts

docs.abstract: Business boomed for JPMorgan Chase and Citigroup last year. Even Wells Fargo, which is struggling with operational problems, managed to make shareholders happy.
docs.snippet: Business boomed for JPMorgan Chase and Citigroup last year. Even Wells Fargo, which is struggling with operational problems, managed to make shareholders happy.
docs.lead_paragraph: Last year was a tumultuous one for American farmers and manufacturers as President Trump squabbled with trading partners around the world. American banks, however, had a ball.

headline.main: Big Banks Ended 2019 on a High Note
headline.print_headline: Big Banks Spin an Anxious Year Into Gold

docs.abstract: Fearful of public anger over a plunging economy, Iran’s leaders appear to be turning inward, pulling back from escalation.
docs.snippet: Fearful of public anger over a plunging economy, Iran’s leaders appear to be turning inward, pulling back from escalation.
docs.lead_paragraph: Iran is caught in a wretched economic crisis. Jobs are scarce. Prices for food and other necessities are skyrocketing. The economy is rapidly shrinking. Iranians are increasingly disgusted.

headline.main: Iran’s Grim Economy Limits Its Willingness to Confront the U.S.
headline.print_headline: Broken Economy May Keep Tehran From Waging War

docs.abstract: Germany and other countries were already vulnerable. The longer the Chinese economy remains crippled, the bigger the risk to the rest of the world.
docs.snippet: Germany and other countries were already vulnerable. The longer the Chinese economy remains crippled, the bigger the risk to the rest of the world.
docs.lead_paragraph: FRANKFURT — So far, only scattered cases of the coronavirus have appeared in Europe, but the economic effects are proving harder to quarantine. The shock may be severe enough to push the vulnerable German economy, and perhaps the entire eurozone, into a recession.

headline.main: Coronavirus Shock Could Push Europe Into a Downturn
headline.print_headline: Virus Putting E.U. at Risk Of Recession

docs.abstract: As the coronavirus spreads, assembly lines may take longer than expected to restart, causing a chain reaction around the world.
docs.snippet: As the coronavirus spreads, assembly lines may take longer than expected to restart, causing a chain reaction around the world.
docs.lead_paragraph: FRANKFURT — Chinese car and car-parts factories may stay closed longer than expected because of the coronavirus, increasing the chances that assembly lines in Asia, Europe and the United States could grind to a halt because of shortages of components.

headline.main: Chinese Car Factories Idled by Virus Raise Risks to Global Growth
headline.print_headline: Auto Industry Squirms as Virus Idles Chinese Plants
